<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND
        CRANKCASE - REAR OIL SEAL AND WEAR SLEEVE - WEAR SLEEVE REMOVAL, Out-of-Chassis
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="0">
        <title>WEAR SLEEVE REMOVAL, Out-of-Chassis</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the flywheel, flywheel housing and rear oil seal carrier removed, use a hammer and tap
                the O.D. of the wear sleeve (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e105_139.xml" xrefid="ef1050717">7.17</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>This causes the wear sleeve to expand and slide off easily.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Discard wear sleeve.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
